article.headline: Montana 73, N. Arizona 54
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- Anthony Johnson scored 16 of his 24 points in the second half as Montana beat Northern Arizona 73-54 Saturday night. Jordan Hasquet had 12 points, 11 rebounds and seven assists for the Grizzlies (16-9, 10-3 Big Sky) while Ryan Staudacher had 12 points and six assists. Shane Johannsen led Northern Arizona (7-17, 4-9) with a career-high 17 points while Zarko Comagic added 14. Montana opened the game with a 10-0 run only to see the Lumberjacks answered with an 11-0 spurt. Neither team was able to pull away until early in the second half when Grizzlies forward Jack McGillis sparked a 16-5 run over 5:19 to give Montana a 45-34 lead. Northern Arizona closed to 45-37 with 10:31 remaining but got no closer.
